   In addition to Danny, who narrates the novel's first and final
sections, we hear from his mother, Helga; from his sister, Bridget;
from the Divins' former cook, Baptie, still living in South Africa;
and from Santi, Danny's first love, now teaching at a university. The
personae and their voices are convincingly distinct, and each of
their narratives provides a fresh perspective on the others.

